phases.content:
Extend the existing `titleTouched` + inline `.issue-form-field-error` pattern in `apps/desktop/src/components/ui/IssueFormModal.tsx` to two more sites:

1. **customBranch** — when `branchStrategy === "custom"`: required, and validate against a practical git-branch-name rule once touched.
2. **body / Enhance with AI** — replace the silent disable on the Enhance dropdown trigger (currently `disabled={... || !body.trim()}`) with a visible `.issue-form-field-hint` beneath the textarea when `body` is empty and Claude CLI is available. The button remains disabled, but the reason is now surfaced.

The issue body's third sub-task (release selection required when 'Add to release' is checked) **does not apply** — the actual UI has no such checkbox; the release `<select>` is always visible with a 'None' option, making it optional by design. Skip it.

### State additions (around line 37, alongside `titleTouched`)

```tsx
const [customBranchTouched, setCustomBranchTouched] = useState(false);
```

No `bodyTouched` is needed — the hint is purely derived from `!body.trim() && claudeCliAvailable !== false`.

### Branch-name validation helper (module scope, above the component)

```ts
/**
 * Practical subset of git's check-ref-format rules. Catches the common bad
 * inputs (empty, leading dot/dash, '..', whitespace, special chars, '.lock'
 * suffix) without trying to reproduce git's full regex — the error message
 * needs to be actionable.
 */
const BRANCH_NAME_FORBIDDEN_CHARS = /[\s~^:?*\[\\@]/;
function validateBranchName(name: string): string | null {
  const v = name.trim();
  if (!v) return "Branch name is required";
  if (v.startsWith("-") || v.startsWith(".")) return "Branch name cannot start with '-' or '.'";
  if (v.endsWith(".lock")) return "Branch name cannot end with '.lock'";
  if (v.includes("..")) return "Branch name cannot contain '..'";
  if (BRANCH_NAME_FORBIDDEN_CHARS.test(v)) return "Branch name cannot contain spaces or any of: ~ ^ : ? * [ \\ @";
  return null;
}
```

### Reset block (around line 103–104) — add the new touched flag

```tsx
setCustomBranchTouched(false);
```

### Custom-branch JSX (around line 537) — add validation wiring

Derive the error once near the top of render:
```tsx
const branchError = branchStrategy === "custom" ? validateBranchName(customBranch) : null;
const showBranchError = customBranchTouched && branchError !== null;
```

Update the custom branch `<input>` to:
- `onBlur={() => setCustomBranchTouched(true)}`
- `aria-invalid={showBranchError}`
- `aria-describedby={showBranchError ? "custom-branch-error" : undefined}`
- Add `className={\`...${showBranchError ? " invalid" : ""}\`}` if the surrounding input doesn't already have a className.

Render beneath the input:
```tsx
{showBranchError && (
  <span id="custom-branch-error" className="issue-form-field-error">
    {branchError}
  </span>
)}
```

### Body / Enhance hint (around the description field, line 342–450)

Change the Enhance dropdown trigger's disabled clause: keep `disabled={loading || enhancing || !body.trim() || claudeCliAvailable === false}` — no functional change to the disable. But also render a hint span beneath the textarea (alongside the existing description label/area) when the body is empty:

```tsx
{!body.trim() && claudeCliAvailable !== false && (
  <span id="body-enhance-hint" className="issue-form-field-hint">
    Add a description to use Enhance with AI
  </span>
)}
```

The hint should appear in the same field-container as the textarea so it sits naturally below.

### Submit-button disable predicate (around line 657)

Extend it:
```tsx
disabled={loading || !title.trim() || (branchStrategy === "custom" && validateBranchName(customBranch) !== null)}
```

### `handleSubmit` (lines 210–260)

Add a pre-submit guard mirroring the existing title check (line 213). If invalid, set `customBranchTouched(true)` so the error becomes visible, and `setError(branchError)` for the global error div (consistent with how the title check uses `setError` already):
```tsx
if (branchStrategy === "custom") {
  const err = validateBranchName(customBranch);
  if (err) {
    setCustomBranchTouched(true);
    setError(err);
    return;
  }
}
```

### Scope boundaries

- Single file: `apps/desktop/src/components/ui/IssueFormModal.tsx`. CSS already has `.issue-form-field-error` and `.issue-form-field-hint` (per the review at lines 227 / 232) — no CSS changes.
- No new dependencies, no Rust changes, no state-shape changes, no IPC.
- The existing title-required pattern is the source of truth — the new validation mirrors its idiom (touched flag → onBlur/onChange → inline span with stable id → aria-invalid/aria-describedby on the input → submit-button disabled predicate update).

### Test plan

- `pnpm build` — clean tsc -b + vite build.
- `pnpm test` — existing 89-test vitest suite green (no IssueFormModal unit tests today; a touched-state unit test is borderline-worth — defer unless an obvious bug surfaces, consistent with v0.6.0's #173–#177 shipping pattern).
- Manual smoke (developer): (a) open the modal, choose "custom" branch, blur with empty value → red error "Branch name is required"; (b) type a leading dot or a space → real-time format error; (c) clear the description while custom-branch is valid → Enhance dropdown stays disabled AND the hint "Add a description to use Enhance with AI" appears; (d) on submit with title empty → existing title error works unchanged.
